Lately 🤍🥲🥹✨

12 months of slow living 🤍💫 

I set a goal this year, to not tie my worth or peace of mind to my level of productivity. Being intentional to build strong, sustainable wellness habits and and use my time to feed my spirit, & giving myself what I need. 
This year had many unexpected challenges, it did not pan out in some of the ways I had hoped. With these last few days, I am working to focus on my wins, treating myself with love and operating from a place of grace, courage and gratitude. 

What slow living looked like for me: 
🤍 prioritizing what feed my soul 
🤍 prioritizing my loved ones and time spent with them 
🤍 prioritizing my wellness and building good habits 

For so long, I determined my value based on how hard I worked, how busy I was, how impressed others were with me, how much others “liked” me, how much I made, etc. 

This year I challenged myself to be present, to add value to my community and loved ones, to be at peace with not always knowing the next steps, to be available for God, to be ready to be awed by a sunrise or a compliment or a small act of kindness. 

This year gave me healing, gave me courage, gave me discipline, gave me rest, and taught me that my softness is my strength. 

I cannot wait for what’s to come 🤍 

In reflection, these are a few things that meant the world to me over the past 51 weeks 🤍💖✨

🤍 creating a home 
🤍 good people 
🤍 exploring my personal style 
🤍 cooking 
🤍 celebrating my body through consistent movement 
🤍 going home for 6 weeks to South Africa 
🤍 personal development through reading, events & online courses

From battling cystic acne to embracing every chapter of this extraordinary journey! 🌟 Welcome to my empowering new series, where I’m opening up about the behind-the-scenes, challenges, scams, and breakthroughs I’ve encountered during my 10-year struggle with acne.

In Part 1, I’m unveiling my 8-month skin transition on Accutane, revealing the true power of persistence, self-care, and a sprinkle of patience 🤍

Throughout my own experience, there were countless things I wish I had known. The lack of representation I saw online made it challenging to make informed decisions or begin the work to feeling confident in my own skin.

Acne not only affects our confidence, but also our peace of mind and sense of identity. That’s why I’m here to create a community of strong, confident women who embrace every step of their journey and build lives they love 🩷

Together, let’s shatter the stigma, inspire unwavering confidence, and wholeheartedly embrace our unique journeys! 💪✨ #SkinJourney #Accutane #SkincareRevolution #Skincare #Acne

I spent most of my childhood in small towns and remember falling absolutely in love with Toronto when I first moved here at 15. ⁠
We took a family drive through the downtown core and I remember passing by the enchanting Gould Street at TMU, where people strolled freely and coffee shop patios beckoned – it was pure fascination! ☕⁠
⁠
Years later, I became one of those happy coffee enthusiasts, cherishing every sip and moment spent in Toronto's bustling atmosphere.⁠
⁠
Over time, the city has evolved and had to overcome. I admit, every once in a while, I found myself yearned for the allure of NYC, the charm of a little European town, or the beauty of Cape Town. 🗽🏰🏞️ But this summer, I'm embracing a different perspective – determined to rediscover the magic of my own city. 💫✨ There are so many exciting experiences I've been putting off, and now it's time to check them off my bucket list, one by one. here you go 👇🏽
✨ what’s working for me this week? 

Perhaps there’s a new habit or mindset you’ve found to be energizing and encouraging! Make sure to note it for next time. Knowing what’s working for you is just as important (if not MORE important) than knowing what isn’t 🤍 

✨ what task/project would be the biggest game changer if I complete it? 

There are 100 things pulling for your attention, resources and response. By mid week it is easy to start feeling the overwhelm. Define and narrow in on the biggest bang for your buck. 
HINT: usually it is something a that you’ve been putting on the back burner or procrastinating on all week. 

✨ how can I re-fuel and get my cup filled? 

Don’t wait for the engine light! Whether it’s making time to call your best friend, asking for extra cuddles, going to bed a bit earlier tonight or going for a walk - get it in! 🤍
